               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; names of the donors; directives to the
                        ministers; titles of books to be read; elements of the punctuation signs;
                        elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD; On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r),
                        a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text is called ʾaslǝṭ in the incipit (fol. 3ra).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="51vb"/>Fol.
                        51va: ይትባረከ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላከ፡ አበውየ፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ በዳህና፡ ወበሰላም። ተጽሕፈ፡
                        በ፲፻ወ፱፻፳ [Fol. 51vb] ፪፡ ዓመት፡ እምልደተ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ በዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጉሥነ፡
                        ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወጳጳስነ።<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The colophon mentions the date 1922 A.M. (=1929/30 A.D.) and King
                           Ḫaylä Śǝllase I (r. 1930-1974).</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
